text: Daniel Quintero Calle (born 26 July 1980) is a Colombian politician. He was the mayor of Medellín since 2020. Quintero was suspended as mayor from 10 May to 21 June 2022 for trying to interfere in the 2022 presidential election. ==Notes== ==References== Category:1980 births Category:Living people Category:Mayors of Medellín Category:Colombian engineers
